  "body": "Problem\r\n\r\nCurrently we use `call-params` function to prepare the parameters for a contract call but this function is very naive and doesn't work with dynamic parameters.\r\n\r\nImplementation\r\n\r\nWrite an `abi-spec` namespace with an encode function that takes the function signature and the parameters values and return the encoded data which can be used to call the contract.\r\n\r\nAcceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nImplementation should work for all exemples of the abi spec\r\nhttps://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/develop/abi-spec.html\r\n\r\nFuture Steps\r\n\r\nThis issue is only about solving the encoding part. Similarly it would be desirable to implement the decoding part to handle return values.\n\n<blockquote><div><strong><a href=\"https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/develop/abi-spec.html\">Contract ABI Specification â€” Solidity 0.4.25 documentation</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
